  "title": "ball_squeeze_Carlton_2025",
  "description": "This dataset comprises high-density functional near-infrared spectroscopy (fNIRS) measurements acquired during a ball-squeeze motor task. The study focuses on optimizing surface-based image reconstruction techniques for high-density fNIRS to improve spatial localization of hemodynamic responses. Data were collected from multiple subjects performing controlled motor movements, providing a resource for validating advanced neuroimaging reconstruction algorithms.",
  "methods_description": "High-density functional near-infrared spectroscopy (fNIRS) data were acquired during a ball-squeeze motor task. The dataset includes raw fNIRS measurements suitable for surface-based image reconstruction analysis.",
